cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the task of inferring spectral signatures from aerial images using deep learning techniques. The paper specifically focuses on the use of conditional adversarial networks for this task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a neural network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning techniques for image processing also suggests the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with aerial imagery, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics).
